text: Skyang Kangri is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in China and Pakistan. It is also known as Staircase Peak. It is the 44th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Hideki Nagata and Yoshioki Fujioji, by the east ridge route in 1976. The expedition was led by G.Mitsui. ==References== Category:Karakoram Category:Mountains of Xinjiang Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan
